  "prompt": "Which US Senate seats are up for reelection in 2018?",
  "response": "In the 2018 United States Senate elections, 35 Senate seats were contested. These included 33 seats whose terms were expiring in 2019 and two special elections. Notable seats up for reelection were held by:\n\n1. Democrats:\n   - Joe Donnelly (Indiana)\n   - Claire McCaskill (Missouri)\n   - Heidi Heitkamp (North Dakota)\n   - Bill Nelson (Florida)\n   - Joe Manchin (West Virginia)\n   - Jon Tester (Montana)\n   - Sherrod Brown (Ohio)\n\n2. Republicans:\n   - Ted Cruz (Texas)\n   - Dean Heller (Nevada)\n   - Roger Wicker (Mississippi)\n\nThere were also special elections:\n- Mississippi (to replace Thad Cochran)\n- Minnesota (Tina Smith, who was appointed following Al Franken's resignation)\n\nOverall, 26 seats were held by Democrats, 9 by Republicans. The election was significant as it offered the Democratic Party a chance to regain control of the Senate, though ultimately, Republicans maintained their majority.",
